                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3548.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Chihuahua</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-09T22:00:00-07:04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1912—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Military authorities have confiscated a large lot of private mail sent by
                    American passenger last night. There is every reason to believe my letter to the
                    Consul at Paso del Norte, containing telegram <pb facs="0894" n="778"
                        xml:id="pg_778"/> to the Department, was included. Said telegram reported
                    the expected shooting of American named Fountaine<note n="1" xml:id="d1037fn1"
                        >Elsewhere spelled Fountain.</note> at Parral this morning. Protested
                    against the act last night and instructed consular agent protest before the
                    military authorities Parral. The newspapers say that Fountaine was shot 5 this
                    morning notwithstanding.</p>
                <p>Attitude rebel authorities insolent toward this office and Americans
                    generally.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
